channel.title: Compile error, i need help, not n00bish
channel.description:
uugh, 2 error and im stumped... the first one sounds stupid, but idk what happened, help plz...
[code] client.java:7954: illegal start of type else if (command.startsWith("answer1")) ^ client.java:11902: <identifier> expected }; ^ 2 errors Starting WarScape v2 Server on 0.0.0.0:43594 [/code]

item.title: Compile error, i need help, not n00bish
item.dc:creator: @mod_taharok Taharok
item.description:
@mod_taharok wrote:

Where was this code put in the client???[br][size=1]Posted at: October 19, 2006, 10:21:16 PM[/size][hr]You need to look at the other commands in this area if its by the other commands. (I believe warscape is a modified Testscape so this should be simple.) If the other commands around it start with “else if”, then your command should work, but if they start with “if”, then take away the “else” on the code you provided and it should work. Also space it so it matched all the other code around it. Another good tip is to keep it in the middle of that section of code and not at the beginning or end of it (causes too many problems to count). This should make your server work. If it doesnt post a reply about any other errors/questions you want answered/you encounter and I will provide help. If I dont after some time then PM me and I WILL GET BACK TO YOU. I hope this helped. Enjoy! =)

~Mod Taharok
